{{Infobox song contest | name = Melodifestivalen | year = 1993 | theme = | logo = | final = 5 March 1993 | presenters = [[Triple & Touch]] | winner = "[[Eloise (Arvingarna song)|Eloise]]" by [[Arvingarna]] | vote = Regional juries decided the final five songs, televotes decided the winner | host = | venue = [[Lisebergshallen]], [[Gothenburg]] | entries = | interval = | opening = }}
'''[[Melodifestivalen]] 1993''' was the selection for the 33rd song to represent [[Sweden]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. It was the 32nd time that this system of picking a song had been used. 1569 songs were submitted to [[Sveriges Television|SVT]] for the competition. The final was broadcast on [[SVT2|TV2]] and [[Sveriges Radio]]'s P4 network. The show was watched by 4,284,000 people, with a total of 166,045 votes cast.
