The '''Metropolitan Opera House''' was a historic [[opera house]] located in [[Saint Paul, Minnesota]] located at 100 East Sixth Street. Plans to build the house began after the [[Grand Opera House (Saint Paul, Minnesota)|Grand Opera House]] burned down on January 21, 1889. Initial plans for the house were designed by [[Leroy Buffington]], but his plans were abandoned due to insufficient funds. Business tycoon [[Robert Mannheimer]] eventually came to the rescue, providing half a million dollars towards the project. New plans by [[Charles A. Reed]] were used for the house which was built over a few months in 1890. The opera house opened for business that year and served as Saint Paul's opera venue until 1936.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=uegmzT1auoQC&pg=RA1-PA226&lpg=RA1-PA226&dq=St.+Paul+Metropolitan+Opera+House&source=bl&ots=JxTiD7Z21E&sig=IQQAyf6zlwaq5LqiEe3DCPtp0wU&hl=en&ei=pzdDStmZHIiwMMqzkasB&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1 Lost Twin Cities By Larry Millett at google books]</ref>

