{{Infobox music festival | name =Mystic Seaport Sea Music Festival | image =File:Jerrybryantatmystic.jpg | caption =[[Jerry Bryant (songwriter)|Jerry Bryant]] performing at the Sea Music Festival 2009 | location =[[Mystic Seaport Museum]] in [[Mystic, Connecticut]] | years_active =1979-present | founders =Dr. Stuart M. Frank | dates =June | genre = [[Maritime music]] | attendance = | capacity = | website = }}
The '''Mystic Seaport Sea Music Festival''', held annually in June since 1979 at the [[Mystic Seaport Museum]] in Mystic, Connecticut, is among the oldest, and is the largest sea [[music festival]] in the United States. It reportedly attracts "the highest caliber of sea music performers, scholars, and fans."<ref>Carr, J.. 2009. New Sea Chantey Compilations On Compact Disc. Review of "American Sea Songs and Shanties " ''Journal of American Folklore'' 122, no. 484, (April 1): 197-210. http://www.proquest.com/ (accessed February 6, 2010).</ref> The Festival was first organized by Dr. Stuart M. Frank as a place to perform and hear [[sea shanty|sea music]] as well as a symposium for ethnomusicologists, anthropologists, and historians.<ref>"Sea Music Festival Comes of Age," ''Mystic Seaport Magazine'', Summer 2009.</ref>
